Maxxd – Privacy Policy
Effective Date: November 9, 2025
Company: Wave State, LLC (“Wave State,” “we,” “us,” or “our”)
Address: 2033 San Elijo Ave #1011, Cardiff, CA 92007
Contact: support@maxxd.io
This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and protect information about users of the Maxxd app (“App” or “Service”).
By using the App, you consent to the practices described in this Privacy Policy. If you do not agree, please do not use the App.
Note: This Policy is designed with principles from applicable privacy laws in mind (including the California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA/CPRA) and the EU General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) where applicable), but you should have a qualified attorney review for your specific compliance needs.
1. Scope
This Privacy Policy applies to information we collect:
Through the Maxxd mobile application;
Through related services and communications;
Through our support channels.
It does not apply to third-party websites, services, or applications, even if accessed through the App.
2. Information We Collect
We collect the following categories of information:
2.1 Account and Profile Information
Name, email address, username, and password;
Basic profile details such as gender, age range, height, weight, fitness goals, and preferences (if you choose to provide them).
2.2 Health, Fitness, and Usage Data
Information about your workouts, exercise history, sets, reps, weights, and performance;
Nutrition data, including foods logged, calories, macronutrients, and related notes;
Progress metrics (e.g., weight changes, body measurements, progress photos if you choose to upload them).
Because this information may relate to your health and lifestyle, it may be considered sensitive personal informationunder certain laws.
2.3 Camera and Photo Data for AI Scanning
When you use our AI Scanning Features, we collect:
Photos captured using your device’s camera within the App;
Photos you choose to upload from your device’s gallery;
Metadata associated with images (where available), such as timestamp or device information.
These images are used to:
Detect and identify food items;
Estimate calories and nutritional content;
Improve and refine our AI models and recognition systems (in an aggregated or de-identified form, where possible).
You must grant camera and/or photo library permissions on your device to use these features. You can revoke permissions at any time in your device settings.
2.4 Device and Technical Information
We may automatically collect:
Device identifiers (e.g., device ID, operating system, app version);
IP address, approximate location derived from IP (not precise GPS unless you separately grant such permissions);
Log data (e.g., usage times, feature interactions, crash reports, and performance data).
2.5 Cookies and Similar Technologies
If we use web-based components or analytics, we may use cookies, SDKs, and similar technologies to:
Remember your preferences;
Analyze usage and performance;
Improve the App.
Where required, we will seek your consent before using certain cookies or trackers.
2.6 Support and Communications
If you contact us, we collect:
Your email address and any other contact information you provide;
The content of your messages and any attachments;
Support and feedback records.
3. How We Use Your Information
We use your information for the following purposes:
To provide and maintain the App
Create and manage your account;
Deliver core features such as workout planning, nutrition logging, and AI scanning;
Sync and display your progress across devices.
To operate our AI and analytics
Process images and data to estimate calories and nutrients;
Improve recognition models, algorithms, and app performance;
Develop new features and functionalities.
To personalize your experience
Provide tailored recommendations, workout suggestions, and nutrition guidance;
Adjust difficulty levels, training volume, or dietary suggestions based on your goals and usage (similar in concept to other AI-powered nutrition and exercise apps, but specific to Maxxd).
To communicate with you
Respond to your requests, questions, and feedback;
Send administrative messages (e.g., account notices, security alerts);
Provide updates about features or changes to our Terms or this Policy.
For security and fraud prevention
Detect, investigate, and prevent misuse or unauthorized access;
Protect the rights, property, and safety of users and Wave State.
For legal and compliance purposes
Comply with legal obligations;
Enforce our Terms of Service;
Respond to lawful requests by public authorities.
4. Legal Bases for Processing (EEA/UK Users)
If you are in the European Economic Area or the UK, we process your personal data under one or more of the following legal bases:
Contract: To provide the App and fulfill our contract with you.
Consent: For certain uses of health-related data, AI processing of images, and marketing communications. You may withdraw consent at any time, but this will not affect processing already performed.
Legitimate Interests: To improve the App, maintain security, and engage in limited analytics, provided our interests are not overridden by your rights.
Legal Obligation: To comply with applicable laws and regulations.
5. How We Share Your Information
We do not sell your personal information in the conventional sense (for money). We may share information as follows:
Service Providers and Vendors
We may share information with third-party providers who perform services on our behalf, such as:
Cloud hosting and storage;
Analytics and crash reporting;
Payment processing (through app stores);
Email and communication tools.
These providers are contractually obligated to protect your information and use it only as instructed.
AI and Model Infrastructure Partners
For AI scanning and model training, we may use external infrastructure or tools. Where we do so:
We seek to de-identify or pseudonymize data whenever feasible;
We impose contractual obligations to protect your data.
Legal and Safety Disclosures
We may disclose information if we believe, in good faith, that such disclosure is reasonably necessary to:
Comply with laws, regulations, or legal processes;
Protect the safety of any person;
Protect our rights or property.
Business Transfers
If Wave State is involved in a merger, acquisition, financing, or sale of assets, your information may be transferred as part of that transaction, subject to continued protection according to this Policy or a successor policy that is at least as protective.
Aggregated or De-Identified Data
We may use and share aggregated or de-identified information (that does not reasonably identify you) for research, analytics, or other lawful purposes.
6. Data Retention
We retain your information for as long as reasonably necessary to:
Provide and improve the App;
Maintain business records;
Comply with legal obligations;
Resolve disputes and enforce our agreements.
We may retain some information in backup or archival copies for a limited period, even after you delete your account, as technically or legally required.
7. Your Choices and Control
7.1 Camera and Photo Permissions
You can control camera and photo access through your device settings. If you disable these permissions:
You will not be able to use certain AI scanning features;
We will no longer collect new camera or photo data through the App, but we may retain previously collected data as described above, unless you request deletion where applicable.
7.2 Account and Profile Information
You may update, correct, or delete certain profile information within the App. For other updates or deletion requests, you may contact us at privacy@maxxd.io.
7.3 Marketing Communications
If we send marketing emails, you can opt out by using the unsubscribe link in the message or contacting us. We may still send non-promotional messages (e.g., account or security notices).
8. Your Privacy Rights
Depending on your location, you may have certain rights regarding your personal information.
8.1 California Residents (CCPA/CPRA)
If you are a California resident, you may have the right to:
Know what categories of personal information we collect, use, and disclose;
Access specific pieces of personal information;
Request deletion of your personal information (subject to certain exceptions);
Correct inaccurate personal information;
Limit the use and disclosure of sensitive personal information (e.g., health data), where applicable;
Not be discriminated against for exercising your privacy rights.
You or your authorized agent may exercise these rights by contacting us at privacy@maxxd.io. We may need to verify your identity before responding.
8.2 EEA/UK Residents (GDPR)
If you are in the EEA or UK, you may have the right to:
Access your personal data;
Request correction of inaccurate or incomplete data;
Request deletion of your data in certain circumstances;
Restrict or object to certain processing;
Request data portability;
Withdraw consent where processing is based on consent.
You also have the right to lodge a complaint with your local data protection authority.
8.3 Other Regions
You may have similar rights under local laws in your jurisdiction. We will honor your rights to the extent required by applicable law.
9. Children’s Privacy
The App is not intended for children under 13, and we do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13. If we learn that we have collected personal information from a child under 13 without appropriate consent, we will take steps to delete it.
If you believe we have collected information from a child under 13, please contact us at privacy@maxxd.io.
10. Security
We use reasonable technical and organizational measures designed to protect your information from unauthorized access, loss, or misuse. However, no system can be completely secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.
You are responsible for maintaining the confidentiality of your account credentials and for any activities that occur under your account.
11. International Data Transfers
We are based in the United States and may process and store your information in the U.S. and other countries with different data protection laws than your home country.
Where required, we will take appropriate safeguards (such as standard contractual clauses or equivalent mechanisms) to ensure an adequate level of protection for your personal data.
12. Automated Decision-Making and Profiling
Maxxd uses algorithms and AI to generate recommendations (e.g., workouts, nutrition suggestions, and calorie estimates). These features:
Are intended to assist and not replace human judgment;
Rely on data you provide and on model outputs that may be imperfect or approximate.
You may choose not to follow any recommendations, and you can stop using the App at any time.
13. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. If we make material changes, we will notify you by updating the “Effective Date” and, where appropriate, providing additional notice (e.g., in-app notice or email).
Your continued use of the App after the updated Policy takes effect indicates your acceptance of the changes.
14. Contact Us
If you have questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy or our privacy practices, please contact:
Wave State, LLC
2033 San Elijo Ave #1011
Cardiff, CA 92007
Email: support@wavestate.co

